<h3>Greptile Summary</h3>

This PR addresses two distinct problems: (1) the ACP verification gate was incorrectly failing persistent-session turns and applying a hard failure banner to oneshot runs that produced real progress output but no tracked file diff — both are now handled more gracefully; and (2) `session.message` payloads arriving during an active chat run are now appended directly to the transcript (with chat-side deduplication and optimistic-echo replacement) instead of discarding the update until the run ends. The `verifyAcpWorktreeDiff` helper and its test coverage look solid; the session-message append path is well-tested for the normal case.

<h3>Confidence Score: 5/5</h3>

Safe to merge; all remaining findings are P2 style/robustness observations with no current defect on the changed path.

The verification-gate logic is correct and well-tested (persistent bypass, oneshot-with-progress → blocked, oneshot-without-progress → failed). The session.message append path handles the active-run guard, deferred reload, and optimistic-echo replacement. The only open items are a potential deduplication gap (only triggers if the server sends messageId without embedding it in the message object, corrected on the next loadChatHistory anyway) and a documentation note about untracked files in the git-diff check — both P2.

No files require special attention.

